A Texas pharmacist made an alarming admission in an anonymous letter to the Texas State Board of Pharmacy last year. The pharmacist wrote, &ldquo;I am a danger to the public working for CVS.&rdquo;
The anonymous letter went on to explain that CVS imposes an &ldquo;absolutely dangerous&rdquo; amount of busy work that pharmacists are expected to do on top of their principal concern of verifying prescriptions.
If this problem isn&rsquo;t isolated, but instead is chain-wide, the risk to patients is staggering.
